ZH: 他跪在地上向老师道歉。
EN: He knelt on the ground to apologize to the teacher.

ZH: 在中国的传统婚礼中，新郎会跪下向双方父母敬茶。
EN: In traditional Chinese weddings, the groom kneels down to serve tea to both sets of parents.

ZH: 当他听到坏消息时，他眼泪夺眶而出，跪在地上哭泣。
EN: When he heard the bad news, tears welled up in his eyes and he knelt on the ground crying.

ZH: 宣誓就职时，国家主席必须跪在宪法上。
EN: When taking the oath of office, the President must kneel on the Constitution.

ZH: 在某些宗教仪式中，信徒会跪下祈祷。
EN: In certain religious ceremonies, believers will kneel down and pray.

ZH: 他跪在父亲的墓前，默默地思念着他。
EN: He knelt in front of his father's grave, silently remembering him.

ZH: 这个牛仔跪在地上打捆绑着犯罪嫌疑人。
EN: The cowboy knelt on the ground, restraining the suspected criminal.

ZH: 当寒冷的土地上有年轻植物时，我总是小心翼翼地跪下拍照。
EN: Whenever there are young plants on the cold ground, I always carefully kneel down to take pictures.

ZH: 他跪在地上，帮助那个老妇人捡起她掉落的包包。
EN: He knelt on the ground and helped the elderly woman pick up her dropped purse.

ZH: 小盆友不听话，妈妈就叫他跪在地上思考。
EN: When the child misbehaves, the mother makes him kneel down on the ground to reflect.

ZH: 他双膝跪地向她求婚，她激动得泪如雨下地答应了。
EN: He got down on both knees and proposed to her, and she tearfully accepted.

ZH: 在武术训练中，学生常常需要跪在地上做伏地挺身。
EN: In martial arts training, students often need to kneel down on the ground and do push-ups.

ZH: 跪姿是一种示敬和忏悔的姿势。
EN: The kneeling position is a gesture of respect and repentance.

ZH: 有时，人们会跪在地上，向祖先祈祷。
EN: Sometimes people kneel on the ground to pray to their ancestors.

ZH: 忍者在夜晚跪伏在屋顶上，等待机会行动。
EN: The ninja knelt on the rooftop at night, waiting for an opportunity to act.

ZH: 在观看仪式期间，观众会跪坐在地上。
EN: During the ceremony, the audience will kneel and sit on the ground.

ZH: 在宫廷电视剧中，臣民常常会跪拜国王。
EN: In palace dramas, subjects often kneel and bow to the king.

ZH: 面对圣地，朝圣者会跪地祈祷。
EN: Facing the holy land, pilgrims kneel on the ground and pray.

ZH: 匆忙行走的人们路过街头艺人，只用淡淡的目光，从容不迫地跪了下去。
EN: Hurrying pedestrians passed by street performers, only briefly glancing and calmly kneel down.

ZH: 她的膝盖受伤了，现在走路只能跪着。
EN: Her knees were injured, so she can only walk on her knees now.

ZH: 小汪跪着看着窗外的风景，心情好像很痛苦。
EN: Xiaowang knelt down and looked at the scenery outside the window, seemingly in great pain.
